Paul Johnson

Software Engineer Intern - SoftGenetics LLC

State College, PA - Email me on Indeed: indeed.com/r/Paul-Johnson/b4273fe29842acb4

Dedicated and passionate software engineer with multiple years of experience in a wide range of programming languages searching for a career where my skills can be applied to create innovation solutions to complex problems. Self-motivated as well as team-oriented - able to work independently and within a team to ensure robust and timely deliverables.

Authorized to work in the US for any employer

WORK EXPERIENCE

Software Engineer Intern

SoftGenetics LLC - January 2017 to Present

Migrated an older Linux server running Tomcat 4.1 in the Java 1.4 SDK Environment to Tomcat 8.1 and developed new services for the system, including a MySQL database API. Created web applications in jQuery/ bootstrap, single page applications in ReactJS and NodeJS rendered web applications in Handlebars. Worked in a team using NodeJS and Electron Forge to create native Windows, MacOS and Linux applications. Wrote tests for React and Handlebars applications with the Jest framework.

Software Engineer Intern

Minitab, Inc - August 2016 to December 2016

Worked on projects among veteran engineers using Microsoft Team Foundation Server with Agile methodology and Git source control with an extensive code review process. Developed applications in C++ and C# to support existing framework, focused primarily but not exclusively on the HOOPS/3dGS library. Utilized CMake to generate cross-platform project files. Used the google C++ test framework to write unit tests for existing code and wrote scripts in Python and Batch to automate these processes.

EDUCATION

B.S. in Applied German

The Pennsylvania State University December 2017

B.S. in Information Science Technology

Pennsylvania State University-Main Campus - State College, PA December 2017

SKILLS

JAVA (4 years), LINUX (Less than 1 year), .NET (Less than 1 year), ANDROID (Less than 1 year), ASP (Less than 1 year)

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

COMPUTER KNOWLEDGE:

Platforms:

• Windows NT/XP/7/10 • Linux

• Android • iOS

Development Software:

• Microsoft Visual Studio .NET 2015 • RStudio

• NetBeans / Eclipse • Microsoft SQL Server 2012

Computer Languages:

• Using and reviewing C++, C# and Python for development and release

• Understanding of Object Oriented design and Agile development approaches

• Using Git source control to collaborate with a team to complete a project

• Programming in Java, J2EE, Hibernate, Spring MVC

• Using ASP .NET with Azure and Node.JS for backend production.

• Creating and managing databases with Microsoft SQL Server and MongoDB

• Web Development with Javascript/Typescript, HTML5, CSS3
